        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:35PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 235 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 12 miles north of Winnfield to 9 miles
south of Richwood, or extending from 12 miles southeast of Jonesboro
to 13 miles southeast of Brownsville-Bawcomville, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbia, Dodson, Sikes, Vixen, Luna, Riverton, Lapine, Fondale,
Bosco and Hudson.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
